<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-05-22T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-05-22T15:00:00-05:00" n="911" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d911">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.44 Sun Yat Sen/39: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-05-22T16:00:00-04:00">May 22, 1929—4
                                p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>169. …</p>
                        <p>Referring to your 384, May 14, 6 p.m.,<note n="92" xml:id="d911fn92">Not
                                printed.</note> Navy Department desires that Commander in Chief U.
                            S. Asiatic Fleet participate officially in the ceremonies and the
                            Secretary of the Navy informs me he has instructed <pb facs="1022" n="878" xml:id="pg_878"/> the Commander in Chief to attend the
                            ceremonies as a member of your special mission and to communicate with
                            you regarding details.</p>
                        <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>